very outcome, not model-output correctness; no text requires evaluating LLM decision quality (REJECTION-GATE). Rejected Workflow: no explicit multiple agentic steps are required.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled report job against test/staging data sources and a real email delivery path to a test inbox. Assert that the inbox receives the message for configured recipients and that core report sections are present end-to-end.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"QUOTE-EVIDENCE: \"email delivery service is unreachable,\" \"saved to a local file,\" and \"retried on the next scheduled run.\" This combines real external-service failure + filesystem persistence + scheduler/run-boundary behavior, which crosses OS/network/time boundaries (REAL-INFRA -> System). Rejected Integration because in-process mocks can miss real retry/persistence/scheduling edge failures. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness here is transport/retry state handling, not model judgment content.","test_description":"Run the job with email service intentionally unreachable in a system-like environment, verify fallback file is written on disk, then trigger the next scheduled run with service restored and assert the pending report is retried and delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
